EXPERIMENT WITH THE MAKE COMMAND:

Note carefully that the indented lines in the makefile begin
with a tab character.  This is a design flaw in the make
utility: the actions specified in a makefile require
the use of an invisible character (a tab).

First use the makefile to create a dependency tree.  Then give
the following command:

   make

What happens on the screen should correlate with your dependency
tree.  If not, you will need help to straighten out your
misconceptions.
